<h4 id="platonic-solids">Platonic Solids</h4>
<p>In three-dimensional space, a Platonic-solid is a regular, convex ployhedron. It
is constructed by congruent(identical in shape and size), regular(all angles 
equal and all sides equal), polygonal faces with the same number of
faces meeting at each vertex.</p>

<h4 id="polyhedron">Polyhedron</h4>
<p>Polyhedron: three-dimensional object made of polygonal faces, meeting along
edges or at a vertex.
<img src="/images/math-structure-simple-group-platonic.png" /></p>

